---
---

<section id="faq" class="py-24 bg-white border-t border-gray-100">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-serif tracking-tight">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 font-sans">
        Everything you need to know about how we work.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      
      <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
      <details class="group bg-[#fcfbf8] rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden open:shadow-md transition-all">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-medium text-gray-900">
          How long until I see results?
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg fill="none" height="24" shape-rendering="geometricPrecision" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600">
          <p>Most of our clients see their first jump in rankings within 30-45 days. By month 3, you should be seeing a noticeable increase in organic calls. SEO is a long-term play, but our local focus means we often get faster results than national campaigns.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
      <details class="group bg-[#fcfbf8] rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden open:shadow-md transition-all">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-medium text-gray-900">
          Do I need to spend money on ads?
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg fill="none" height="24" shape-rendering="geometricPrecision" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600">
          <p>No. Our entire strategy is built around organic visibility. We get you ranked in Google Maps and standard search results so you get traffic without paying for every click. Once you're ranking, that traffic is yours.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
      <details class="group bg-[#fcfbf8] rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden open:shadow-md transition-all">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-medium text-gray-900">
          What if I'm already with another SEO company?
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg fill="none" height="24" shape-rendering="geometricPrecision" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600">
          <p>We can seamlessly take over. We'll run a full audit of what they've done, keep the good stuff, and fix the bad. Many of our best clients came to us after being disappointed by generic agencies who didn't understand local service businesses.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
      <details class="group bg-[#fcfbf8] rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden open:shadow-md transition-all">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-medium text-gray-900">
          Is there a lock-in contract?
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg fill="none" height="24" shape-rendering="geometricPrecision" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600">
          <p>We ask for an initial 3-month commitment because SEO takes time to build momentum. After that, it's completely month-to-month. We keep our clients by delivering results, not by locking them into 12-month contracts.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
      <details class="group bg-[#fcfbf8] rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden open:shadow-md transition-all">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-medium text-gray-900">
          What exactly do I get for $500/month?
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg fill="none" height="24" shape-rendering="geometricPrecision" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600">
          <p>You get the complete local dominance playbook: Google Business Profile optimisation, ongoing Maps ranking management, on-page SEO targeting your specific services, technical site fixes, and our automated 5-star review engine. Everything is handled for you.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
      <details class="group bg-[#fcfbf8] rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden open:shadow-md transition-all">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-medium text-gray-900">
          How is this different from other SEO companies?
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg fill="none" height="24" shape-rendering="geometricPrecision" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600">
          <p>We only work with local service businesses. We don't do e-commerce, we don't do national brands. We know exactly what it takes to get a local business to the top of the map pack in their specific area, and we execute that exact playbook relentlessly.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  details > summary {
    list-style: none;
  }
  details > summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }
</style>
